1.

Requirement:
“System shall generate monthly accounts payable summary reports.”

Ambiguity (Completeness):

“summary reports”

Why:

It doesn’t define what data should be included in the summary, so developers may include different information than what users expect.
2.

Requirement:
“System shall allow users to approve invoices before payment processing.”

Ambiguity (Unambiguity):

“users”

Why:

It’s unclear which users (e.g., managers, accountants) are allowed to approve invoices, which could lead to incorrect access control.
3.

Requirement:
“System shall store vendor contact information including name, address, and phone number.”

Ambiguity (Completeness):

“address”

Why:

It’s not clear what fields are required for an address (e.g., street, city, ZIP code), so implementations may vary.
4.

Requirement:
“System shall validate invoice entries before submission.”

Ambiguity (Meaningfulness):

“validate”

Why:

“Validate” is unclear without rules—developers don’t know what checks to perform (e.g., required fields, format, duplicates).
5.

Requirement:
“System shall allow users to search invoices by date and vendor.”

Ambiguity (Unambiguity):

“date”

Why:

It’s unclear whether this refers to invoice date, due date, or payment date, which could affect search results.
6.

Requirement:
“System shall maintain a history of payment transactions.”

Ambiguity (Completeness):

“history”

Why:

It doesn’t specify how long the history should be stored (e.g., 1 year, indefinitely), leaving the requirement incomplete.
7.

Requirement:
“System shall notify users when invoices are overdue.”

Ambiguity (Unambiguity):

“overdue”

Why:

It’s unclear how overdue is defined (e.g., 1 day late, 30 days late), which affects when notifications are triggered.
8.

Requirement:
“System shall allow editing of vendor records.”

Ambiguity (Meaningfulness):

“editing”

Why:

It’s unclear what parts of the vendor record can be changed and whether there are restrictions.
9.

Requirement:
“System shall support exporting reports in standard formats.”

Ambiguity (Completeness):

“standard formats”

Why:

The requirement doesn’t specify which formats (e.g., PDF, CSV, Excel), so developers may choose differently than expected.
10.

Requirement:
“System shall restrict access to financial data based on user roles.”

Ambiguity (Completeness):

“user roles”

Why:

It doesn’t define what roles exist or what permissions each role has, making the requirement incomplete.
